  "text": "Following the definition of emergence [CITATION_1] as a phenomenon occurring suddenly in a complex system consisting of a sum of simpler entities and being inspired by the behavior observed in cellular automata, for example (as in Conway's Game of Life, for one) and at the same time perceiving the whole computing system proposed here as a simulation of \"living beings,\" we try to leverage the emergence phenomenon in order to properly configure the computing system without the need for doing datafarming-related experiments, checking thousands of different configurations of the system parameters. Even if we found an optimal one, it would not be equally best for all of the considered problems (cf. no free lunch theorem [CITATION_2] ). Thus, we try to define the simple actions of individuals that affect the structure of the population, eventually hoping for stabilization and the attainment of good quality in the produced solution.",
